#: src/faq.md:1
msgid "FAQ"
msgstr ""

#: src/faq.md:3
msgid ""
"Answers to the questions first-time visitors ask before reading any of the "
"detailed pages. Each answer links to where the topic is covered in full."
msgstr ""

#: src/faq.md:6
msgid "What is AI Agent Assembly, in one sentence?"
msgstr ""

#: src/faq.md:8
msgid ""
"It is a **governance layer for AI agents**: it sits between your agents and "
"the outside world and enforces policy, tracks cost, and intercepts unsafe "
"actions _before_ they run. See the [Introduction](README.md) and [Why AI "
"Agent Assembly?](comparison.md)."
msgstr ""

#: src/faq.md:13
msgid "Do I have to change my agent's code?"
msgstr ""

#: src/faq.md:15
msgid ""
"Not necessarily. There are three interception layers and you can pick how "
"invasive to be:"
msgstr ""

#: src/faq.md:18
msgid ""
"The **SDK layer** needs a small amount of instrumentation in your code and "
"is the fastest path."
msgstr ""

#: src/faq.md:20
msgid ""
"The **sidecar proxy** (`aa-proxy`) governs an agent's network traffic with "
"**no code change**."
msgstr ""

#: src/faq.md:22
msgid ""
"The **eBPF sensor** (`aa-ebpf`, Linux only) catches actions at the kernel "
"level, including bypass attempts."
msgstr ""

#: src/faq.md:25
msgid "See the three-layer interception model in the [Introduction](README.md)."
msgstr ""

#: src/faq.md:27
msgid "Does it work with my LLM / framework?"
msgstr ""

#: src/faq.md:29
msgid ""
"Yes — it is provider-agnostic. It governs agents regardless of which model "
"provider you use, and ships SDKs for **Python, TypeScript/Node, and Go**, "
"with framework examples (LangChain, LlamaIndex, bare OpenAI, and more) in "
"the [examples repository](https://github.com/ai-agent-assembly/examples)."
msgstr ""

#: src/faq.md:34
msgid "Is it free? What is open source vs. paid?"
msgstr ""

#: src/faq.md:36
msgid ""
"The enforcement core — the interception layers, policy engine, SDKs, and CLI "
"— is **open source under Apache-2.0**. Enterprise operations (SSO, SCIM, "
"tamper-evident audit, dedicated regions, SLAs) are commercial and delivered "
"on paid SaaS tiers. See the [Open core boundary](open-core-boundary.md)."
msgstr ""

#: src/faq.md:41
msgid "Can I self-host it?"
msgstr ""

#: src/faq.md:43
msgid ""
"You can self-host a **limited-function** stack from the open-source crates "
"(using the published Docker Compose example) for local evaluation and "
"development. The **complete** feature set is delivered through the AI Agent "
"Assembly cloud (SaaS). See the [Open core boundary](open-core-boundary.md)."
msgstr ""

#: src/faq.md:48
msgid "How does it actually block an unsafe action?"
msgstr ""

#: src/faq.md:50
msgid ""
"Before an agent action runs, the gateway evaluates your policy and returns "
"an allow or deny decision; a deny stops the action. Budgets are enforced the "
"same way — once a team is over budget, further calls are denied. See the "
"[Policy reference](policy-reference.md)."
msgstr ""

#: src/faq.md:55
msgid "How is it different from an observability / tracing tool?"
msgstr ""

#: src/faq.md:57
msgid ""
"Observability tools record what an agent _did_, after the fact. AI Agent "
"Assembly makes a binding **allow/deny decision before the action executes**. "
"The [comparison page](comparison.md) maps this against other tools."
msgstr ""

#: src/faq.md:61
msgid "Where do I get started right now?"
msgstr ""

#: src/faq.md:63
msgid ""
"Clone the [examples "
"repository](https://github.com/ai-agent-assembly/examples) and run a "
"governed agent end to end — that is the path you can run today. The managed "
"[Quick start (SaaS)](quickstart-saas.md) is coming soon."
msgstr ""

#: src/faq.md:67
msgid "What do the acronyms mean (eBPF, SCIM, mTLS, STRIDE…)?"
msgstr ""

#: src/faq.md:69
msgid ""
"See the [Glossary](glossary.md), which defines every recurring term and "
"acronym in plain language."
msgstr ""

#: src/security-model.md:1
msgid "Security model"
msgstr ""

#: src/security-model.md:3
msgid ""
"AI Agent Assembly is a **governance layer for AI agents** — it enforces "
"policy, tracks cost, and intercepts unsafe actions before they run. This "
"page documents the security posture behind that enforcement, for enterprise "
"security and compliance teams. It covers the layered defense model, a STRIDE "
"threat analysis, the cryptography in use, and the audit and compliance "
"posture."
msgstr ""

#: src/security-model.md:7
msgid "IronClaw five-layer defense"
msgstr ""

#: src/security-model.md:9
msgid ""
"AI Agent Assembly groups its security controls into five named layers. Each "
"layer is independently deployable and adds defense-in-depth — if one layer "
"is bypassed, the next still applies."
msgstr ""

#: src/security-model.md:11
msgid "Layer"
msgstr ""

#: src/security-model.md:11
msgid "Name"
msgstr ""

#: src/security-model.md:11
msgid "What it does"
msgstr ""

#: src/security-model.md:13
msgid "1"
msgstr ""

#: src/security-model.md:13
msgid "**Boundary**"
msgstr ""

#: src/security-model.md:13
msgid ""
"Network perimeter: sidecar proxy (`aa-proxy`) enforces egress policy; eBPF "
"sensor (`aa-ebpf`) catches kernel-level bypass attempts"
msgstr ""

#: src/security-model.md:14
msgid "2"
msgstr ""

#: src/security-model.md:14
msgid "**Identity**"
msgstr ""

#: src/security-model.md:14
msgid ""
"Agent and user authentication: JWT-based agent identity issued by the "
"gateway; operator authentication via SAML 2.0 / OIDC SSO"
msgstr ""

#: src/security-model.md:15 src/cloud-deployment.md:44
msgid "3"
msgstr ""

#: src/security-model.md:15
msgid "**Policy**"
msgstr ""

#: src/security-model.md:15
msgid ""
"Runtime governance: YAML/JSON policy rules evaluated by the gateway policy "
"engine before every agent action"
msgstr ""

#: src/security-model.md:16
msgid "4"
msgstr ""

#: src/security-model.md:16
msgid "**Vault**"
msgstr ""

#: src/security-model.md:16
msgid ""
"Secret and credential management: AES-256-GCM encryption at rest for stored "
"secrets; Ed25519-signed tokens for inter-component trust"
msgstr ""

#: src/security-model.md:17 src/cloud-deployment.md:44
msgid "5"
msgstr ""

#: src/security-model.md:17
msgid "**Telemetry**"
msgstr ""

#: src/security-model.md:17
msgid ""
"Audit and observability: append-only event log for every agent action; "
"Slack/webhook connectors for real-time alerting on policy violations"
msgstr ""

#: src/security-model.md:19
msgid ""
"**How the five layers relate to the three interception points.** The five "
"_defense-in-depth layers_ above (Boundary, Identity, Policy, Vault, "
"Telemetry) describe _what_ is protected. The three _interception points_ "
"named on the landing page and marketing site — the SDK layer, the sidecar "
"proxy (`aa-proxy`), and the eBPF sensor (`aa-ebpf`) — describe _where_ "
"enforcement is applied, and all three sit inside the **Boundary** layer. "
"They are two views of one system, not two competing models."
msgstr ""

#: src/security-model.md:23
msgid "STRIDE threat model"
msgstr ""

#: src/security-model.md:25
