#: src/comparison.md:62
msgid ""
"These are capabilities competitors offer that AI Agent Assembly does not yet "
"fully deliver."
msgstr ""

#: src/comparison.md:64
msgid ""
"**Vault-backed secrets management** — Pillar Security provides first-class "
"secrets vault integration with automatic secret rotation and injection. "
"AAASM currently supports secret-pattern detection via regex policies but "
"does not integrate with HashiCorp Vault or AWS Secrets Manager."
msgstr ""

#: src/comparison.md:65
msgid ""
"**Automated human-in-the-loop approval workflows** — Pillar Security "
"provides structured approval routing with escalation chains. AAASM can deny "
"and alert but does not yet route decisions to a named approver queue."
msgstr ""

#: src/comparison.md:66
msgid ""
"**Full-function self-hosted deployment** — Langfuse, Opik, and Pillar "
"Security offer a fully self-hostable product. AAASM self-hosting is "
"limited-function today: a limited stack runs locally from the Apache-2.0 "
"crates (Docker Compose) for evaluation and development, while the complete "
"feature set is delivered via SaaS (see [Open Core "
"Boundary](open-core-boundary.md))."
msgstr ""

#: src/comparison.md:67
msgid ""
"**Evaluation frameworks and LLM-as-judge scoring** — Langfuse and Opik "
"provide built-in evaluation pipelines, dataset management, and automated "
"LLM-as-judge scoring for output quality. AAASM's policy engine operates on "
"patterns and metadata, not semantic quality."
msgstr ""

#: src/comparison.md:68
msgid ""
"**Prompt management and versioning** — Langfuse provides a managed prompt "
"registry with version history and A/B comparison. AAASM does not include a "
"prompt registry."
msgstr ""

#: src/comparison.md:72
msgid "Where we lead"
msgstr ""

#: src/comparison.md:74
msgid ""
"These are capabilities where AI Agent Assembly is uniquely strong or "
"differentiated."
msgstr ""

#: src/comparison.md:76
msgid ""
"**Pre-execution runtime enforcement** — AAASM is the only product in this "
"comparison that makes binding allow/deny decisions _before_ an agent action "
"executes. All others are observability tools that record what happened after "
"the fact."
msgstr ""

#: src/comparison.md:77
msgid ""
"**Kernel-level bypass detection via eBPF** — `aa-ebpf` intercepts TLS calls "
"at the SSL library level using Linux uprobes, catching bypass attempts that "
"SDK-only solutions cannot see. No competitor in this matrix offers "
"kernel-level enforcement."
msgstr ""

#: src/comparison.md:78
msgid ""
"**Network-layer interception without code changes** — `aa-proxy` performs "
"MitM HTTPS interception via a per-host CA. Governance can be applied to "
"agents that do not use the SDK. No competitor supports sidecar-proxy-level "
"enforcement."
msgstr ""

#: src/comparison.md:79
msgid ""
"**Policy-as-code with GitOps workflow** — AAASM policies are YAML/JSON "
"documents that can be versioned, reviewed, and deployed via standard Git "
"workflows. No competitor in this matrix offers a structured policy language; "
"guardrails in other tools are typically configured through UI forms or "
"proprietary DSLs."
msgstr ""

#: src/comparison.md:80
msgid ""
"**Immutable tamper-evident audit log** — AAASM's audit log entries are "
"signed with HMAC-SHA256, making post-hoc alteration detectable. This is a "
"compliance requirement in regulated industries (PCI-DSS, SOC 2 Type II) that "
"no competitor in this matrix fully addresses."
msgstr ""

