#: src/self-host-observability.md:23
msgid "Health and readiness probes"
msgstr ""

#: src/self-host-observability.md:25
msgid "`aa-runtime` — `/health` and `/ready`"
msgstr ""

#: src/self-host-observability.md:27
msgid ""
"The runtime runs a combined health/metrics HTTP server bound to "
"`AA_METRICS_ADDR` (see [Metrics endpoint](#prometheus-metrics-endpoint) "
"below for the env var and its default). It serves two probe routes:"
msgstr ""

#: src/self-host-observability.md:29
msgid ""
"**`GET /health`** — liveness. Returns `200 OK` with a JSON body reporting "
"`status`, process uptime, events processed, and which enforcement layers are "
"active or degraded. Use this as a liveness probe."
msgstr ""

#: src/self-host-observability.md:30
msgid ""
"**`GET /ready`** — readiness. Returns `200 OK` (body `ready`) once the "
"runtime is ready to accept work, or `503 Service Unavailable` (body `not "
"ready`) before then. Use this as a readiness/startup gate."
msgstr ""

#: src/self-host-observability.md:32
msgid ""
"```console\n"
"$ curl -fsS http://localhost:8080/health\n"
"{\"status\":\"healthy\",\"uptime_secs\":42, ...}\n"
"\n"
"$ curl -fsS http://localhost:8080/ready\n"
"ready\n"
"```"
msgstr ""

#: src/self-host-observability.md:40
msgid "`aa-gateway` — `/healthz`"
msgstr ""

#: src/self-host-observability.md:42
msgid ""
"The gateway exposes a process-liveness probe at **`GET /healthz`** in both "
"of its run modes. It returns `200 OK` with a small JSON body as long as the "
"gateway is responding to HTTP:"
msgstr ""

#: src/self-host-observability.md:44
msgid ""
"**local mode** reports `mode: \"local\"` with SQLite-backed storage (local "
"mode also mounts `/api/v1/health`)."
msgstr ""

#: src/self-host-observability.md:45
msgid ""
"**remote mode** reports `mode: \"remote\"` with `postgres` or in-memory "
"storage depending on how it is configured."
msgstr ""

#: src/self-host-observability.md:47
msgid ""
"```console\n"
"$ curl -fsS http://localhost:<gateway-port>/healthz\n"
"{\"mode\":\"local\",\"version\":\"...\",\"storage\":\"sqlite\",\"uptime_secs\":...}\n"
"```"
msgstr ""

#: src/self-host-observability.md:52
msgid ""
"The gateway's HTTP port depends on how you launch it in the Docker Compose "
"example — check your compose file's port mapping rather than assuming a "
"fixed value."
msgstr ""

#: src/self-host-observability.md:54
msgid "`aa-api` — `/api/v1/health`"
msgstr ""

#: src/self-host-observability.md:56
msgid ""
"The REST API exposes a health check at **`GET /api/v1/health`** (all API "
"routes are nested under `/api/v1/`). It returns `200 OK` when every "
"subsystem check passes, or `503 Service Unavailable` when any is degraded. "
"The JSON body includes the build `version`, `api_version`, uptime, and a "
"`checks` map with per-subsystem status for the policy engine, registry, "
"audit, and alerts."
msgstr ""

#: src/self-host-observability.md:58
msgid ""
"```console\n"
"$ curl -fsS http://localhost:<api-port>/api/v1/health\n"
"{\"status\":\"ok\",\"version\":\"...\",\"api_version\":\"v1\",\"checks\":{\"policy_engine\":\"ok\", "
"...}}\n"
"```"
msgstr ""

